  <static seed="1156" source="Contrib/PCC/BasicAlgebra/RationalExpressionAlgebraSkills/simplifyRationalExpressions170.pg">
    <statement><p>Simplify the following expression, and if applicable, write the restricted domain on the simplified expression.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{{\frac{t^{4}+8t^{3}+15t^{2}}{t^{4}+7t^{3}+12t^{2}}}=}</m> <fillin characters="19" name="AnSwEr0001"/></p>
</statement>
    <answer>
      <p>
        <m>\frac{t+5}{t+4}, t\ne -3\hbox{ and }t\ne 0</m>
      </p>
    </answer>
    <solution><p>To simplify the expression, we first factor both the numerator and denominator, and then cross out common factors:</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{\begin{aligned}
   {\frac{t^{4}+8t^{3}+15t^{2}}{t^{4}+7t^{3}+12t^{2}}} \amp = \frac{{t^{2}\mathopen{}\left(t^{2}+8t+15\right)}}{{t^{2}\mathopen{}\left(t^{2}+7t+12\right)}} \\
                     \amp = \frac{{t^{2}\mathopen{}\left(t+3\right)\mathopen{}\left(t+5\right)}}{{t^{2}\mathopen{}\left(t+3\right)\mathopen{}\left(t+4\right)}} \\
                     \amp = {\frac{t+5}{t+4}, t\ne -3\hbox{ and }t\ne 0}
\end{aligned}
    }</m></p>
<p>Since the factors <m>t^{2}</m> and <m>t+3</m> were crossed out, the domain conditions lost during the simplification are <m>t \ne 0</m> and <m>t \ne -3</m>.</p>
</solution>
